Peru Stocks: Southern Copper, Cerro Verde, Volcan, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-02-15T18:58:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/peru-stocks-southern-copper-cerro-verde-volcan-relapasa.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:43 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index dropped 0.6 percent to 22,858.95.
The MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.2 percent to 3,084.60.  Miners slumped after copper, zinc and lead declined in New
York and London, said Daniel Romero, an analyst at Lima-based
investment fund NC&F Inversiones SA.  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., fell 1.9 percent to $51.  Southern Copper Corp . (SCCO PE), Peru’s biggest copper producer,
dropped 1.1 percent to $44.10. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA
(VOLCAAC1), Peru’s biggest zinc producer, fell 1.1 percent to
4.50 soles.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, fell 1.5 percent to 1.95 soles after crude oil
dropped to a two-month low in New York.  Soc. Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and lead
producer, advanced 1.6 percent to 56.50 soles after announcing
fourth-quarter net income rose 23 percent to $35.4 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  